observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to direct:
a. The concerned Implementing Offices to expedite the implementation of the PPAs to utilize the fund transfers within the prescribed period, and observe strictly the parameters set in the Memorandum of Agreement;
b. The Municipal Accountant to exhaust efforts in retrieving the supporting documents and expediting the return of the unexpended balances to the Source Agencies;
c. The Municipal Accountant to send confirmation letters to the Source Agencies to validate the balance per books of the prior years’ unutilized fund transfers; and
d. The Municipal Treasurer to coordinate with the concerned implementing offices upon receipt of fund transfers from various NGAs for the timely implementation by the said offices of the PPAs and prompt recording of their subsequent liquidation.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to direct:
The concerned Implementing Offices to expedite the implementation of the PPAs to utilize the fund transfers within the prescribed period, and observe strictly the parameters set in the Memorandum of Agreement;
The Municipal Accountant to exhaust efforts in retrieving the supporting documents and expediting the return of the unexpended balances to the Source Agencies;
The Municipal Accountant to send confirmation letters to the Source Agencies to validate the balance per books of the prior years’ unutilized fund transfers; and
The Municipal Treasurer to coordinate with the concerned implementing offices upon receipt of fund transfers from various NGAs for the timely implementation by the said offices of the PPAs and prompt recording of their subsequent liquidation.

We recommended and that the Local Chief Executive agreed to require the MEEDO Head to:



Facilitate the execution and renewal of all lease contracts as soon as possible;

Come up with a more proactive collection scheme to encourage the timely payment of monthly rentals;

See to it that the outstanding balance of delinquent stall owners are properly monitored and collected;

Impose strictly surcharges and consider the termination of contracts in view of late payments once the contracts are renewed; and 
Ensure that the contracts of lease are renewed annually on or before the expiration of the previous contract.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Direct the PRAISE Committee to establish mechanisms for identifying, rewarding and providing incentives to deserving employees at the start of the year;

Require the officers and employees of the municipality to refund the monetary incentive given as the requirements for the grant of monetary awards were not met as required by regulation.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

Reclassify the fund transfer from Donations to Due from other LGUs;
Monitor and demand the liquidation reports from the recipient LGUs;
Comply with the requirements provided in COA Circular No. 2012-001 and other pertinent laws, rules and regulations.

We also recommended that the MPDO submit copy of the agreed policy and procedures in the monitoring of PAPs and the corresponding report thereon.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Stop the payment of monetary awards to job hire / contract hire and strictly comply Section V, Item No. 3 of the Civil Service Commission Memorandum Circular No. 38 and Section 4 of DBM Budget Circular No. 2010-1;

Require the Job hire / Contractual employees of the municipality to refund the monetary incentive given as they are not entitled to such.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

Reclassify the fund transfer from General Fund to Trust Fund;

Adhere strictly with the provisions of General Appropriations Act of 2016, COA Circular No. 94-013 and other pertinent laws, rules and regulations.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Stop the payment of monetary awards if there is no monetary savings identified to have resulted from the suggestions, inventions, superior accomplishments and other personal efforts of employees-grantees;

Direct the PRAISE Committee to establish mechanisms for identifying, rewarding and providing incentives to deserving employees at the start of the year;

Require the officers and employees of the municipality to refund the monetary incentive given as the requirements for the grant of monetary awards were not met as required by regulation.
